  45:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The DMA channel fetch and execute all DMA linked-list queue from first node (head nod
  46:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               node). When last node is executed, the DMA channel fetches the first circular node an
  47:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               the same sequence in an infinite loop (Circular transfer). To stop the DMA channel, a
  48:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               required. This linked-list mode replaces the legacy circular transfers.
